{
  "stem": "24814.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we caught up with them toward the end of November, just as they turned and started their bloody fighting in the Siegfried Line and the Maginot Line positions.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, the-- the big ones we have battle stars for are called Ardennes-Alsace, Rhineland, Central Europe.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They give you a campaign star for each campaign.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We started out fighting our way through the old French Maginot Line forts from the wrong side, the ones that the French couldn't hold against the Germans.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "As the Germans retreated, they dug in their tanks behind these 20-foot concrete pill boxes.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were attacking through heavy mud all along the German-Lorraine border.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In our first battle, we went over the border and attacked the little place called Ottweiler, Germany, the first town in Germany that our division liberated.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was-- they have a big sign, you are entering Germany courtesy of the 12th Armored Division and so on.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then we stopped on the line, Christmas, and just heavy line slugging, through mud and pill boxes and burning villages, very heavy fighting.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then we were told to hold in place.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We didn't know it, but the Belgian Bulge had broken out right on our left flank.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So the division next to us, 3rd Army, went up to attack the Bulge.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were part of Patton's 3rd Army.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We stretched our lines and held in place.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then when the Belgian Bulge slowed down, started to lose its impetus, Hitler and his generals switched to the Alsace-Lorraine, the second phase of the Bulge, to try and take it back.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we were alerted for movement.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The 7th Army, which held that end of the front was a veteran group.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They'd been in Italy.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They'd fought their way up from Marseilles.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They were well prepared.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
